ZCZC GE59
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
TUESDAY TO FRIDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND
COASTGUARD AGENCY AT 222300 UTC
AN AREA OF LOW PRESSURE 991 CENTERED OVER IRELAND ON
TUESDAY EVENING MOVS ACROSS THE IRISH SEA AND THE UK
OVERNIGHT INTO WEDNESDAY. THIS FLN AS IT DOES AND
LOOSING IT IDENTITY AS IT MOVS INTO THE N SEA ON
WEDNESDAY. AT THE SAME TIME HIGH PRESSURE LIES ACROSS
NERN NORWAY. A LARGER AREA OF LOW PRESSURE IN THE N
ATLANTIC ALSO GRADUALLY MOVS E BECMG CENTERED NW OF THE
UK BY THURSDAY MORNING. THIS BECOMES A SLOW MOV BROAD
AREA OF LOW PRESSURE PERSISTING NW OF THE UK AND
DOMINATING CONDITIONS ACROSS CULLERCOATS FRIDAY. A WEAK
RIDGE PERSISTS TO THE S AND E ACROSS CONTINENTAL EUROPE.
STRG WINDS ARE EXP ACROSS NERN CULLERCOATS TUESDAY
BEFORE STRENGTHENING TO NEAR GALES WEDNESDAY WITH ISOL
GALES POSS IN THE FAR NE. OCCASIONAL STRG WINDS ALSO
LIKELY THROUGH DOVER STRAITS. NEAR GALES CONTINUE NE
CULLERCOATS THURSDAY BEFORE GRADUALLY EASING N INTO
